Choosing the Right KPIs for Your Business

Not all KPIs are created equal. Selecting the right ones depends on your business model, industry, and growth stage.

Key questions to ask:

What are our primary revenue goals?

Which customer actions most influence revenue?

Where do deals typically stall in the funnel?

Which channels drive high-intent leads?

For demand generation and ABM programs, effective KPIs often focus on:

Account engagement score

Opportunity-to-close rate

Pipeline velocity

Marketing-sourced revenue

The goal is relevance, not volume.

Common KPI and Metrics Mistakes Businesses Make

Even mature organizations fall into measurement traps.

Frequent mistakes include:

Treating all metrics as KPIs

Tracking vanity metrics with no revenue impact

Ignoring sales alignment when defining KPIs

Failing to update KPIs as strategies evolve

Overloading dashboards with unnecessary data

Avoiding these pitfalls requires clarity, cross-functional collaboration, and regular performance reviews.

